\begin_layout Standard

This procedure results in groups if disjoint labels but can contain overlapping feature-spaces. Labels are clustered based on feature scores, which can be seen as weight of the features impact on the decision about the label. Thus labels in the same cluster share the same features they depend on. Features are only added if they exceed a threshold, to avoid adding unnecessary or disturbing features.
